{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Abu Dawud","section":{"35":"Combing the Hair (Kitab Al-Tarajjul)"},"section_detail":{"35":{"hadithnumber_first":4159,"hadithnumber_last":4213,"arabicnumber_first":4159,"arabicnumber_last":4213}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":4193,"arabicnumber":4193,"text":"Rapporté par Ibn ‘Umar رضي الله عنه : Le Messager d’Allah ﷺ a interdit le qaza’. Le qaza’ consiste à raser une partie de la tête d’un garçon et à laisser une autre partie non rasée","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Muhammad Muhyi Al-Din Abdul Hamid","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Sahih Bukhari (5920) Sahih Muslim (2120)"}],"reference":{"book":35,"hadith":35}}]}